content: Having tested Speedometer Pro daily over the past six months on both Samsung S5 and S6, I have observed that when traveling in hilly terrain speed errors occur as high as 6 KMH above the actual speed, These speed spikes are indicative of a lack of smoothing in the software in the way GPS strings are processed and averaged. The satellite reception is never less than 10 satellites and normally 16 satellites. The speed error or spikes will occasionally occur on flat sections of roadway but is most pronounced when descending, where the greatest spike anomalies are recorded. This lack of smoothing is borne out by observing the operating app in a stationary situation displaying a a speed of up to 3 KMH. I have a requirement for a very accurate highest recorded speed and real time speed (100 - 110 KMH). Any assistance you can offer will be gratefully accepted.
replyContent: The app is completely dependent on the GPS connectivity. We strived to get the as precise readings as possible from the GPS but at the end of the day it is what GPS sends to the app. Please give it a try when you go for a walk/ run. This way, the app will have the best possible connectivity. Let me know if it again shows incorrect spikes.
